Plot the histogram and fit for one subject*condition.

  • yellow = guessing component
  • light blue = Gaussian component
  • green = sum of the guessing and Gaussian components. In other words, the histogram heights predicted by the model
  • dark blue = continuous Gaussian. This helps get a sense of the effect of discretising the Gaussian. For instance, its possible for the Gaussian peak to rise high above the bars and still fit the discrete bins, suggesting undesirably high estimates of the efficacy (likely accompanied by an undesirably low precision)

For likelihood, lower neg log likelihood means better fit.
